01/02/2007
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia -- Kosovo Prime Minister Agim Ceku and KFOR Commander Lieutenant General Roland Kather urged the public Wednesday (January 31st) to refrain from violence, in light of UN special envoy Martti Ahtisaari's visits to Pristina and Belgrade on Friday. He will be presenting his proposal for the status settlement. Ceku, Kather and UNMIK police representatives met on Wednesday to discuss the situation. Kather said that KFOR is on full alert and was ready to ensure that the situation in Kosovo remains under control after Ahtisaari's proposal is unveiled. (Blic - 01/02/07; KosovaLive, B92, Focus, Beta - 31/01/07)
